Medium_supplements: L-glutamine, penicillin, streptomycin, MEM, non-essential amino acids
Differentiation_protocol:
SHSY-5Y neuroblastoma cells were plated on a
96-well plate and cultured in a humidified 5% CO2 atmosphere in
Dulbeccos modified Eagles medium (MEM): F-12 (1:1) with phenol
red, to which L-glutamine, penicillin, streptomycin, MEM, non-essential amino acids, 10% fetal bovine serum (FBS), 0.5% DMSO, and
10 lM all-trans-retinoic acid (RA) as differentiating agent were added.
After 8 days, the supernatant was removed with a pipette and a new
medium (with 2% FBS), free from phenol red, DMSO, and RA, was
added to each cell

Culture_medium: 1:1 minimum essential medium (MEM) and Ham’s F12
Differentiation_medium: 1:1 minimum essential medium (MEM) and Ham’s F12
Differentiation_protocol:
For the neuronal differentiation, when the density
reached nearly 90%, SH-SY5Y cells were maintained in the
medium containing 10 μM retinoic acid (RA, R106320,
Aladdin, Shanghai, China) for 14 days. Then, the morphological
changes were identified RA-induced differentiated SH-SY5Y
cells by inverted-phase contrast microscope
